# Application Structure

## Routing Structure
The application follows Next.js 13+ App Router convention:

- `/src/app/page.tsx` - Homepage
- `/src/app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with common UI elements
- `/src/app/blog/` - Blog section
- `/src/app/realizacje/` - Portfolio/Projects section
- `/src/app/api/` - API endpoints

## Key Sections
- **Blog**: Contains blog posts and related components
- **Realizacje**: Showcases portfolio items and projects
- **API**: Backend API routes for dynamic functionality

## Global Styles
- [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - Global styles and Tailwind directives

## Important Notes
- All pages are server components by default
- API routes are handled in the `/app/api` directory
- Static assets should be placed in the `public` directory
- Components should be organized by feature in `src/components`




